cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.DL, cs.LG

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper discusses creating online databases of language resources and proposes an ontological structure for effective natural language processing.
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also likely as the paper discusses the architecture of OLAC for creating online databases of language resources.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper proposes an extension of OLAC architecture for effective natural language processing.
- cs.DL (Machine Learning) is a possible category as the paper discusses the advantages of an ontological structure over statistical methods for natural language processing.
- cs.LG (Learning) is a possible category as the paper discusses the advantages of an ontological structure over statistical methods for natural language processing, which is a subfield of machine learning.
